<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>
.container {
    position: relative;
    text-align: center;
    color: white;
}
.centered {
    position: absolute;
    top: 50%;
    left: 50%;
    transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
}
</style>
</head>
<body>

<h2>Image Text</h2>
<p>How to place text over an image:</p>

<div class="container">
  <img src="img_fjords_wide.jpg" alt="Norway" style="width:100%;">
  <div class="centered">Centered</div>
</div>

</body>
</html> 
